
'''* Book: The Return of Nature. by John Bellamy Foster.'''

URL =


=Review=

Peter Critchley:

"In a period when environmental problems are being addressed through institutional, technological, and financial fixes, John Bellamy Foster's The Return of Nature is a timely reminder of the deeper, systemic, approach required for an effective response to what is at heart a socio-ecological crisis arising from within the specific forms mediating the human-nature interchange. In this comprehensive, insightful, and highly readable intellectual history, Foster presents a well-researched and richly detailed analysis of a range of thinkers who were the first to identify and systematically address the problems that beset us in the contemporary world. In recovering the intellectual roots of the eco-socialist response to environmental crisis, the book makes it clear that an increasingly pervasive crisis has systemic causes and demands a similarly systematic response."

(https://www.academia.edu/44495145/The_Return_of_Materialist_Dialectics_Review_of_The_Return_of_Nature_by_John_Bellamy_Foster)


